SUBLIME TEXT TRICKS!

## CMD + /: BLACKOUT

Comment out current line.


## CMD + CTRL + G: UNIVERSAL SUMMONS

select code then press CMD + CTRL + G will select ALL of the identical codes


## CMD + D: ONE-LINE SUMMON

select code and press CMD + D will select next same piece of code as well (good for batch changing variable names)


## CMD + SHIFT + D: DOUBLE TEAM
duplicates a line of code the cursor is on


## CTRL + CMD + up/down: DOUBLE PASSE(SERGIO'S BECKONING)

move line/lines up and down


## CMD + (K, B):

show/hide the file explorer on the left side
(Excellent to use when doing a STT/Terminal Split Screen)

## CMD + T:

quick switch between files


## CTRL + F:

search within current tab

## CTRL + SHIFT + F:

search within the folder (all the files)

## CMD + SHIFT + P:

open command pallete, access most commands in sublime text

## CMD + SHIFT + left [ or right ]

select previous / next tab

## CMD + W:

close current tab

## CMD + SHIFT + T:

undo close tab

## CMD + Z:

undo edit

## CMD + SHIFT + Z:

redo
------------------
## CMD + [
REMOVE TAB in line

## CMD + ]
ADD TAB in line

??? ## OPTION + SHIFT + F: ???
## CMD + SHIFT + P:  then type: Reindent

auto indent the code selected, or the whole page without any selection
????
